  #i-just-want-to-git-to-know-you
    %h3.title
      %a{href:'/events.html#data-viz-dave-columbus'}Oct 6th 2015: I just want to "Git" to know you
    %p Teaching Git is hard! (almost as hard as it is to learn)

    %p Git is a big deal and I want you all to learn it too. Deep down I think Git is pretty easy if you see it as a pattern of buttons to click in order. But it can get messy fast when you are working with others.

    %p My goal is not to teach you how to fix all the kinds of conflicts that you can generate with Git. I will show you the best practices when working with Git so you can avoid most of them.

    %h5 We will cover:
    %ul.list
      %li Repositories and their histories
      %li Why you should trust Git
      %li Branching and Merging
      %li Collaborating and Merging conflicts (with tools that make life easier)
      %li The mighty rebase (Love it and Fear it)

    %p
      To register for this event please
      %a{href:"https://www.facebook.com/groups/westmorelandoss/"}join WOSS

    %h5 Agenda:
    %ul
      %li 6:00pm - Install Party for Git and Lightning talks
      %li 7:00pm - Presentation on git and time to work on examples
      %li 9:00pm - Questions discussion
